This script reads the input from standard input, solves the problem using the provided algorithm, and prints the result to standard output. The algorithm first finds the longest increasing subsequence and its reverse. Then it checks each element in the array to see if changing it would make the subsequence strictly increasing. If so, it updates the maximum length of the subsequence. The maximum length found is the answer to the problem.

The time complexity of this algorithm is O(n), where n is the number of elements in the array. This is because we are scanning the array twice to find the longest increasing subsequence and its reverse, and then scanning it once more to check each element. The space complexity is O(1) as we are not using any additional space that scales with the input size.

